<br>
I agree mostly. Especially things like, cuz and joo, but if I'm fighting I use shorthand like b4, u, etc because I am trying to get information out at the same time and I have limited time to do so and drive my toon. But in normal, non combat conversation I always use full words.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Your idea of what a farmer is obvioulsy differs than mine. Hunting with my guild to acquire upgrades for myself and others is not what I would classify as farming. Hunting a trivial mob for loot you don't need for the sole purpose of selling or twinking is (at least in my opinion) Rangers tracking hounds to sell furs is farming, wizards killing dragons to twink out alts is farming, hunting in a challenging zones with my guildes to upgrade our armor isn't /shrug -<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You presuppose the antecedent. All wizards are twinking alts, but you always are nobly helping yourself or your guild. This is just hogwash. The loot from most things I kill, burned or otherwise, goes to my guildmates. I do not apologize for helping them over people I do not know. As I assume you do not.<br>
<br>
Further the whole idea is assinine. If rangers suck as hard as you say then how else are they supposed to acquire money to buy gear so they don't suck so hard?<br>
<br>
It may shock you to know that even level 60 rangers and druids DO get xp from Velium Hounds. Why should they not make use of their tracking ability so they can make some money as well? Which ultimately goes to buying gear which makes them better?<br>
<br>
I don't like paying for VH furs, but I did. Those rangers and druids provided a service, which I paid for. I can make xp LOTS faster than I would killing VH. I think the price was too high at the beginning but the market takes care of that in time.<br>
<br>
In the real world, people grow crops, WAY more than they 'need' to feed themselves, and SELL the excess and have the audacity to use the proceeds to selfishly help their own family, or even themself. How terrible. How avaricious.<br>
<br>
Yet, in America, we consider 'Farming' to be a noble occupation.<br>
<br>
Your entire argument, to the extant that it is one, is an economic position which has been roundly debunked by history. People that promote that position have always proven to be doing so to pursue a personal agenda. Which is always to talk other people out of taking something so they can have more, or failing that, to rally popular support to do it by force.<br>
<br>
So you ask: How much is enough?<br>
<br>
Ask yourself that question. The day you stop trying to improve Montyy the toon will be the day you can answer that question with any moral authority at all.<br>
<br>
Or the day you stop working because, hey, you HAVE enough money and it's greedy to try to get any more than you really need.<br>
<br>
Until then, you are 'farming' just like everyone else in the game. Just like everyone else in the real world.<br>
<br>
Working your best to acquire gear to better yourself, your guild, and your friends.<br>
<br>
