<br>
And FK, there is a HUGE dif between an entire guild going to ToV, Ssra or any other high end zone to better themselves as a unit then 5 people porting to a zone clicking a button and blasting a dragon to bits.  Raiding a high end zone takes skill, and planning, burning a dragon requires 5 wizards to be online, port into a zone, med to full, and hit one button....not much skill involved there.<br>
<br>
Also hunting in ToV or Ssra isn't taking any gaming content away from anyone, yeah theres lots of competition for these zones, but at least its fair competition....if Ssra mob_01 pops and Guilds_01, 02 and 03 go for it, they all prolly have as much chance of getting that mob, as opposed to Mid_level_Guild_01 has against 5 wizards who can all be in the zone and ready in less than 5 min.<br>
<br>
And let me clear up my thought's on Farming....we all use this term, as do I, like Milikin said, farming EXP, farming faction, farming armor....because sadly the way VI set up SoV and SoL, this is basically what you have to do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The farming I am refering to is the repeated killing of a mob with the sole purpose of selling the loot, a great example of this being when druids used to farm the AC in Sro just to sell the ring for MQ.  Why did they do this? cuz they they could, they had the means (track) to beat anyone else there, and now wizards have the means (manaburn) to beat anyone to the kunark dragons...now the only dif being instead of Jboots MQs, its Pally Epic MQs or Bard or warrior epic sales, or dragon haste, not to mention rare kunark spells like Malo and Torpor...same thing on a grander scale.<br>
<br>
And FK, b4 you get all pissy, I'm not questioning that you give all you burn loot away, but Ive seen enough dragon loot in auction channels from wizards in the last few months to know that you are in the minority there.<br>
