<br>
Why? Because there's more people? Because 5 ppl is more efficient? And?<br>
<br>
What is morally different about 40 people killing something versus 5?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Also hunting in ToV or Ssra isn't taking any gaming content away from anyone.. - Montyy<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Horseshit.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The farming I am refering to is the repeated killing of a mob with the sole purpose of selling the loot.. - Monty<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
What do you with your loot that you don't need? Give it away to friends? Sell it for upgrades? How is it different?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> And FK, b4 you get all pissy, I'm not questioning that you give all you burn loot away, but Ive seen enough dragon loot in auction channels from wizards in the last few months to know that you are in the minority there. - Montyy<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Understood. Some do. Some don't. I know there are scales in the bazaar right now. For 15k or less, which to be honest is not a bad price. But even the wizzies who sell them use the proceeds to upgrade their own gear. Why is this wrong? At those rates it will take half a dozen scales to buy a Mana Robe. (btw I've had my robe for a year and bought it with proceeds from tailoring)<br>
<br>
When I started this conversation I had the idea that it was somehow wrong to sell epic pieces. But over the course of these discussions I have thought about it quite a bit. I don't know if I think that anymore. I'm starting to warm up to the idea anyway. If someone can buy a book or a scale for 10k (which you will admit is peanuts), that seems a lot better than trying to organize raids and camping a mob for a day.<br>
<br>
A scale from a burn represents the work of 5-6 people for 30-45 min, with about an 80% success rate. (yes burns do fail despite all your 'no challenge' rhetoric) A scale from a regular raid has almost 100% success rate, but represents the work of a few people for 1-24 hours (camping) and 25-40 people for about 90 minutes, and thus has a much higher overhead. This is why scale prices have dropped so much.<br>
<br>
Anyway, like I said. All this will be moot soon. Midlevel guilds will soon be able to field full, in house, burn teams and it will be them 'stealing' midlevel content. It will be insane to try to organize a traditional raid for these mobs when there's better things to do with those resources. Why send 30 when you can send 5?? No one will, of course. Leading a raid is too much damned work, when there's an easier way.<br>
<br>
Only guilds with too few or no burners of their own will suffer, but really they will only suffer in ability to compete for epic drops.<br>
<br>
