Why? Because the burn team can fail and not have a second chance where a regular raid can repeat until successful? Because if it doesn't fail a burn team is a more efficient? Because a regular raid uses the same tired old MT strategy and the burn team doesn't? VS is the only one that's even the slightest bit interesting.<br>
<br>
What is magic about 30 that's different from 5 or 6?<br>
<br>
To me a traditional MT raid is the REAL gimp encounter. A regular MT raid <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> will</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> suceed. May screw it up the first time, but then more ppl are there and you go again. Wash, rinse, repeat. Rarely does it take 3 tries.<br>
<br>
If burners fail that's it. Game over. Not too likely the mob will be still up in 2hours 20min.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> .. but at least we have a CHANCE. - Montyy<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Newsflash. There are not always enough burners available to kill these mobs. Usually burners don't camp these mobs. Someone hears it's up and then sees who is available. Who knows how long they have been up at this point. If burners show up and there's a raid forming they have simply left. Today Faydedar was up until he suicided on the Iksar Master and no one bothered to kill him. Red scale down the tubes for lack of interest.<br>
<br>
This whole don't have a 'CHANCE' thing is cowchips. VoR wanted Sev they camped him they killed him. Wow. Amazing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Thats what competition is. - Montyy<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Competition, yes, it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> is</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Well how convenient that YOU get to decide who is a valid competitor and who is not. Who is farming, or bottom feeding, or wasting a spawn trying to take something that you think they have no chance to take.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> How would you feel if clerics started running around and killing VS and Phinney every time they poped because they got a new AA ablility that let em do it. - Montyy<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well I wouldn't like it if I had camped VS or Phinny and they steamrolled me. Because, you know, I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> did</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> camp those mobs. You know old fashioned wait for the mob to spawn because I need the drop. How <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> unjustly</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I sufferred in having to actually CAMP the mob. Poor me.<br>
<br>
But I really don't think most clerics would steamroll me, any more than I would steamrol anyone else.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You are taking away the ability for someone to, wait, I'm thinking of the word here.. Talasar<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Tal, you don't know what you are talking about. Every epic piece I have won has gone to a guildmate. Not even a twink. And despite Montyy's uninformed claims of how much I burn these mobs I have only won <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> two</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
But regardless there is a very complicated and closely guarded secret of how someone may get one of these mobs for their epic, and yes, even get to use the marvelously innovative MT strategy on them if they wish.<br>
<br>
I will let the secret out now. Here in public forum, for all the world to see.<br>
<br>
The secret is: Camp the mob.<br>
<br>
Yep. It's tricky, I know, but what you do is park your butt in the zone with a tracker.. and you wait around until the mob pops, and here's the kicker.. then you get some people to come help you kill it. Bet you never thought of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> that</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> did you? Well I felt generous today, it being Friday and all, so I thought I'd let the cat out of the bag. It's all very complicated but I have confidence most people can manage it if they just try.<br>
<br>
Not only that, if you don't happen to have enough friends online at the time that the mob pops, which is certainly possible, you can even, if you have to, send a tell to an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> evil farming burner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and ask her to help you. Burners have been known to take short breaks from their relentless orgy of greedy farming to help people get thier epic drops.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Should we never ever kill anything that doesnt give us exp? - Gaelron<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It is noteworthy that all kunark bosses give xp.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ..dragons were meant to be an encounter of epic proportions that would require multiple groups and still be a tough challenge.. manaburn takes any difficulty away.. - Sephrok<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
These mobs are over two years old and two expansions old. They are not a challenge anymore, sorry.<br>
<br>
Because they can try until they succeed, traditional raids almost never lose to these mobs.<br>
<br>
But burners do.<br>
<br>
There's more risk involved in a burn raid. You have 5-6 fragile wizards against one dragon. Many factors can go wrong. (One can even accidentally burn herself;P) And if it fails, it's over. No do over.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> MB is just overpowering and there is no compensation to other classes other than maybe Rangers from what i can think of. - Sephrok<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Really most classes did well with class AA. Mages, Warriors, and maybe SK's didn't do so well, and those class abilities need to be looked at asap IMO. There's nothing really worth the work for them.<br>
<br>
